The call centre, with a capacity of receiving 100 calls simultaneously.It is expected to play a complementary role in preventing, disrupting and deterring serious crimes. A toll-free crime reporting hotline – 0800722203 -- has been launched for use by Kenyans anonymously.
Speaking during its launch, Mr George Kinoti, the Directorate of Criminal Investigations (DCI) boss, said the line is housed at a modern call centre within the directorate’s offices, in partnership with the UK Government’s National Crime Agency (NCA).



