The call centre will be manned at all hours by specially vetted DCI officers from different fields, who are trained in customer relations and who can speak several languages, including Somali, French, German, Spanish, Arabic, Chinese and Italian.
Mr Kinoti, who was accompanied by Mr James Duddridge, the minister for Africa at the UK’s Foreign Commonwealth & Development Office, UK Ambassador to Kenya Jane Mariot and Mr John Gachomo, the head of the Anti-Terror Police Unit, said all the information received will be analysed and acted upon in real time.  



