“The information given will form a prima facie ground upon which appropriate operations will be planned and executed after the information has been analysed by the appropriate units,” said Mr Kinoti.
The call centre, with a capacity of receiving 100 calls simultaneously, went live on Thursday and is expected to play a complementary role in preventing, disrupting and deterring serious crimes in the country and beyond the borders.
It will also assist the directorate in forming a sustainable intelligence database that will help in formulation of strategies that help manage crime.
Informer's identity
“The identity of the caller is completely encrypted so as to shield, insulate and protect the identity of the informer,” said Mr Kinoti.



